Wash and dry produce. Drain and rinse @cannellini beans{1%unit}. Halve @tomato{1%unit}; thinly slice into half-moons. Slice @mini cucumber{1%unit} into rounds. Quarter @lemon{1%unit}. Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1%unit}; separate leaves. Reserve a few whole leaves for wraps; chop remaining lettuce into bite-size pieces.

In a #large bowl{}, combine beans, tomato, and cucumber; season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Wrap @flour tortillas{2%units} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with paper towels; season with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @vegan mayo{4%tablespoon}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @hot sauce{1%teaspoon}, half the @dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, 1 1/2 tsp @soy sauce{2%teaspoon}, and juice from half the lemon (for 4 servings, use all the mustard, 3 tsp soy sauce, and juice from whole lemon). Season generously with pepper.

> TIP: If dressing seems too thick, add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

In a separate small bowl, whisk together @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, juice from remaining lemon wedges, salt, and pepper.

Place tortillas on a clean work surface. Spread tortillas with half the Caesar dressing. Place filling on the bottom third of each tortilla. Top with lettuce leaves and drizzle with as much remaining Caesar dressing as you like.

Fold up bottom side of each tortilla over filling, then fold over left and right sides toward the filling. Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to form wraps. Wipe out #bowl{}.

In bowl used for filling, toss chopped lettuce with lemony dressing and @sliced almonds{1/2%ounce}.

Slice chicken crosswise; add to tortillas along with filling.

Halve wraps on a diagonal; divide between plates. Serve with salad on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.